{
  "stem": "1858.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And parallel to that we built another wall from old bricks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You had to descend to the bunker from the floor above, but always somebody with a green card.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Green card, that was like, that meant that you were employed, and that your employment was necessary.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "These people were, for the time, being safe, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "If you had to hide in the bunker, somebody like that would have to be left behind and block, or some put-- push something over the entrance so they wouldn't discover that you are there.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was helpful maybe a little bit from the beginning, but later as they came with dogs, and there was no way of escaping.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From beginning, yes he did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you know, those raids, in order to-- you know, from beginning they would come loud, and you would hear the boots.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But soon the Nazis learned to creep up-- up on you like a cat, quietly.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in order to be able to make it to the bunker, many nights people would have to sit on the roof and keep guard and warn the people inside the building that there is a-- a-- there is a raid approaching.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And whenever my father had to sit on the roof, I would go with him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as horrible as those nights might have been, they hold such pleasant memories in my heart for me alone because, you know, we were seven children.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father really never had the time for me alone.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And here on the roof, I had my father all to myself, just for me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was here on the roof that my father would be telling me about his childhood, about my grandparents whom I did not remember much.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
